text:
Irving Ave., west from Covert Street, showing a panoramic view of Brooklyn. The N.E. corner of Covert and Irving Ave. (right foreground, pipes thereon) is in Queens County. The factory at the right is that of Wm. Greilich and Sons Brass Goods Manufacturing Company at the S.W. corner of Eldert Street and Irving Ave.

December 1924.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Covert Street (left foreground; under construction), at the S.W. corner of Irving Ave. (right, partially seen), showing in the foreground a vacant corner upon which, in 1928, was erected a three story brick apartment. The factory at the right, located on the S.W. corner of Eldert Street (parallel to Covert Street) and Irving Ave., is that of Wm. Greilich and Sons.

December 1929.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
